messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full request path:
- /api/products/{id}

All methods acceptable:
- all methods: false

HTTP methods (based on the code):
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: true
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- server.js mounts the product routes with app.use('/api/products', productRoutes); so every route in routes/productRoutes.js is prefixed with /api/products.
- In routes/productRoutes.js the route for a single product is defined as router.route('/:id') and attaches .get(..., getProductById), .put(..., updateProduct) and .delete(..., deleteProduct). That yields the full path /api/products/:id â€” represented here as /api/products/{id} (with the path parameter in curly braces).
- The code explicitly registers handlers for GET, PUT and DELETE on that path, so those methods are acceptable.
- The code does not explicitly register handlers for HEAD, POST, OPTIONS, TRACE or PATCH on this path; per your instruction to base acceptability on the code (not runtime/Express implicit behavior), those methods are marked unacceptable.
- The "all methods" flag is false because there is no route that accepts all methods for this path.
